- **Title:** Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)  
  **URL:** `https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html` ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor / Cyclin-K glue-degrader.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))
  - “Clinical trial details can also be found on www.clinicaltrials.gov under study ID: NCT06600789.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))
  - “The clinical trial is enrolling patients with advanced solid tumors, including ovarian, breast and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))

- **Title:** Carrick Therapeutics Announces U.S. FDA Clearance of IND for CT7439, a First-In-Class Inhibitor of CDK12/13  
  **URL:** `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/20/carrick-therapeutics-announces-u-s-fda-clearance-of-ind` ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/20/carrick-therapeutics-announces-u-s-fda-clearance-of-ind))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “the Company’s Investigational New Drug (IND) application for CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/20/carrick-therapeutics-announces-u-s-fda-clearance-of-ind))
  - “The Company plans to initiate the Phase 1 clinical trial in the first half of 2024 and intends to enroll patients with advanced solid tumors, including breast, ovarian and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/20/carrick-therapeutics-announces-u-s-fda-clearance-of-ind))
  - “CT7439 is an inhibitor of CDK12/13 as well as a 'glue degrader' of Cyclin-K” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/investors/news-events/press-releases/detail/20/carrick-therapeutics-announces-u-s-fda-clearance-of-ind))

- **Title:** Trial | NCT06600789 (Clinical Drug Experience Knowledgebase)  
  **URL:** `https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/` ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “Trial | NCT06600789” ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))
  - “CT7439 Capsules (0.5 mg, 1mg, 3mg)” ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))
  - “Phase 1/Phase 2” ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))

- **Title:** A Modular Phase 1/2 Study With CT7439 in Participants With Solid Malignancies (CenterWatch)  
  **URL:** `https://www.centerwatch.com/clinical-trials/listings/NCT06600789/a-modular-phase-1-2-study-with-ct7439-in-participants-with-solid-malignancies` ([centerwatch.com](https://www.centerwatch.com/clinical-trials/listings/NCT06600789/a-modular-phase-1-2-study-with-ct7439-in-participants-with-solid-malignancies))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “Treatment  CT7439 Capsules (0.5 mg, 1mg, 3mg)” ([centerwatch.com](https://www.centerwatch.com/clinical-trials/listings/NCT06600789/a-modular-phase-1-2-study-with-ct7439-in-participants-with-solid-malignancies))
  - “Clinical Study ID  NCT06600789” ([centerwatch.com](https://www.centerwatch.com/clinical-trials/listings/NCT06600789/a-modular-phase-1-2-study-with-ct7439-in-participants-with-solid-malignancies))
  - “Prior therapy with a specific CDK12/13 inhibitor, within any timeframe prior to thefirst dose of CT7439.” ([centerwatch.com](https://www.centerwatch.com/clinical-trials/listings/NCT06600789/a-modular-phase-1-2-study-with-ct7439-in-participants-with-solid-malignancies))

- **Title:** FDA Clears IND Application for First-in-Class CDK12/13 Inhibitor (CancerNetwork)  
  **URL:** `https://www.cancernetwork.com/view/fda-clears-ind-application-for-first-in-class-cdk12-13-inhibitor` ([cancernetwork.com](https://www.cancernetwork.com/view/fda-clears-ind-application-for-first-in-class-cdk12-13-inhibitor))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “CDK12/13 inhibitor CT7439” ([cancernetwork.com](https://www.cancernetwork.com/view/fda-clears-ind-application-for-first-in-class-cdk12-13-inhibitor))
  - “The compound is a “glue degrader” of Cyclin-K” ([cancernetwork.com](https://www.cancernetwork.com/view/fda-clears-ind-application-for-first-in-class-cdk12-13-inhibitor))
  - “including breast cancer, ovarian cancer, and Ewing sarcoma.” ([cancernetwork.com](https://www.cancernetwork.com/view/fda-clears-ind-application-for-first-in-class-cdk12-13-inhibitor))

- **Title:** Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “SR-4835, a highly selective dual inhibitor of CDK12 and CDK13, which disables triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC) cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))
  - “Keywords:  BRCAness; CDK12; CDK13; PARP inhibitor; cisplatin; intronic polyadenylation; triple-negative breast cancer.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))

- **Title:** Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “a potent PROTAC degrader PP-C8” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))
  - “PP-C8 demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with PARP inhibitor in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC).” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))
  - “Keywords:  CDK12; Cyclin K; PROTAC; Synthetic lethality; Triple-negative breast cancer.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))

- **Title:** Discovery of ZLC491 as a Potent, Selective, and Orally Bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC Degrader (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/))
  - “the discovery of ZLC491 as a potent, selective, and orally bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC degrader.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/))
  - “degraded CDK12 and CDK13 with DC_{50} values of 32 and 28 nM” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/))

- **Title:** Discovery of a Highly Potent and Selective Dual PROTAC Degrader of CDK12 and CDK13 (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))
  - “The optimal compound 7f effectively degraded CDK12 and CDK13 with DC_{50} values of 2.2 and 2.1 nM” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))
  - “by employing the proteolysis-targeting chimera (PROTAC) technology.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35938508/))

- **Title:** The CDK12 inhibitor SR-4835 functions as a molecular glue that promotes cyclin K degradation in melanoma (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/))  
  **Direct quotes (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**
  - “including THZ531 and SR-4835.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/))
  - “SR-4835 uniquely promotes cyclin K degradation via the proteasome.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/))
  - “SR-4835 acts as a molecular glue” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/))
